## IDENTITY & PHILOSOPHY

This is WhereToSkiNext.com (WTSN) - a ski resort decision engine. It helps a skier find
the best mountain for a SPECIFIC DAY based on live snow forecast, drive time, pass
affiliation, crowd outlook, and ticket price. It returns ONE confident recommendation,
not a generic ranked "Top 10" list. The scoring engine is the product.

The engine assigns each resort one of four roles for the day:
- Top Pick      - the single best call
- Solid Option  - a strong alternative
- Worth a Look  - a non-obvious mountain that is genuinely the better play
- Crowd Watch   - good on paper, but the crowd outlook is a real risk

Product philosophy (never violate these):
- Ship over endless iteration. A working feature beats a perfect one.
- The scoring engine is the product. Determinism and transparency are the trust foundation.
- Surface the genuinely better mountain, even when it is small or lesser known. The product
  exists to beat the obvious-destination default, not reinforce it.
- Editorial independence is the credibility basis. Ranking order is never for sale.
- Scoped, minimal changes only. No unrequested refactors, rewrites, or "improvements."
- Every edit should be explainable to a non-coder in plain English.

