## STACK - READ THIS FIRST BEFORE SUGGESTING ANYTHING

- Vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript only. No frameworks whatsoever.
- Deployed on Vercel (Hobby/Free plan) via GitHub Desktop. No CLI deploy workflow.
- Serverless functions live in /api/ and run as Vercel functions.
- Static pages are pre-generated via Node scripts (generate-mountain-pages.mjs,
  generate-state-pages.mjs, generate-city-pages.js). They are not server-rendered at
  request time.
- No frontend bundler and no framework build. The only build-time steps are the Node
  generation scripts above and the scoring obfuscation script (obfuscate-scoring.mjs),
  all run manually before a deploy. Scripts are loaded into pages via <script> tags.
- Node.js is used only for the generation scripts, the obfuscation script, and /api/
  serverless functions.

Supporting services in the live stack:
- Supabase    - analytics tables and the crowd feedback table (anon-key inserts, RLS on)
- Beehiiv     - newsletter distribution (free plan: Send API is blocked, manual paste only)
- Anthropic API - newsletter copy and resort content generation (copy only, never scoring)
- Open-Meteo  - weather forecasts (non-commercial free tier)
- OSRM        - drive times, served from a precomputed 35-cluster matrix with live fallback

NEVER suggest:
- React, Vue, Svelte, Angular, or any frontend framework
- Webpack, Vite, Parcel, or any bundler
- TypeScript (unless explicitly asked)
- npm packages for the frontend
- Replacing <script> tag imports with ES module bundling
- Rewriting existing working logic "for cleanliness"

