## KEY FILES - WHAT EACH ONE DOES

### Core Application
- sd-app.js              Main application logic, UI rendering, the day-input flow, and the
                         rendering of all four role cards (Top Pick, Solid Option, Worth a
                         Look, Crowd Watch). Largest and most sensitive file. Edit carefully.

- sd-scoring.js          The scoring engine. Computes base quality, applies the crowd
                         penalty, and produces the final score each resort is ranked by.
                         normalizedWeights() is CRITICAL: it must always return dynamic
                         weights derived from input, never hardcoded fixed values. A past
                         bug where it returned fixed weights regardless of input broke the
                         whole engine. Never touch normalizedWeights() without explicit
                         instruction.

- recommendation-roles.js  Assigns the four roles (Top Pick / Solid Option / Worth a Look /
                         Crowd Watch) from computed scores. The "Worth a Look" obviousness
                         test lives here: it must not surface obvious destinations. Role
                         assignment reads from scores, never the other way around.

- sd-filters.js          Filter logic for the results set (pass, region, drive radius, etc).

- sd-data.js             Resort data loader. Uses vm.runInNewContext() to parse resort data
                         because JSON.parse() silently fails on JS object literal syntax.
                         Do NOT change this parsing approach.

- resorts.js             Raw resort dataset. All resort entries with stats, pricing,
                         coordinates, terrain, pass affiliation, lift capacity tier, etc.
                         Data quality here directly affects recommendation quality.
                         (NOTE: if the live repo still names this resorts-national.js,
                         that is the same file. Use whichever name the repo actually has.)

### Static Page Generation
- generate-mountain-pages.mjs  Generates one page per mountain (currently 300, across 37
                               states). Run with Node when resort data changes.
- generate-state-pages.mjs     Generates the state landing pages (currently 37).
- generate-city-pages.js       Generates the "from <city>" drive-origin landing pages.

### Serverless Functions (/api/)
- /api/weights.js              Serves scoring weights to the frontend (paired with the
                               obfuscation step). Treat as part of the scoring path.
- /api/crowd-feedback.js       Writes user crowd feedback to the Supabase crowd_feedback
                               table. This is the primary validation path for the crowd model.
- /api/newsletter-generator.js Runs the full engine across all mountains and builds the
                               weekly regional newsletter copy via the Anthropic API.
- /api/geo.js                  Silent IP-derived location seeding for first-time origin.
- /api/subscribe.js            Beehiiv email subscription handler. Reads BEEHIIV_API_KEY
                               and BEEHIIV_PUBLICATION_ID from Vercel env. Never hardcode.

