## SCORING SYSTEM - NEVER BREAK THIS

The scoring system is the entire product. Three things must always hold.

1. NON-COMPENSATORY ARCHITECTURE. The final score is base quality MULTIPLIED BY a crowd
   penalty. Crowd is non-compensatory: a crowded day cannot be rescued by excellent snow or
   any other factor. A big mountain losing to a smaller one on a crowded Saturday is the
   CORRECT output, not a bug. The big mountain winning back a quiet midweek day is the proof
   the model works. Do not "fix" this by letting other factors buy back a crowd penalty.

2. THE CROWD MODEL PREDICTS, IT DOES NOT MEASURE. It reasons from stable structural inputs
   (metro proximity / gravity, pass-network pull, destination draw, lift capacity tier) plus
   logistic soft-clamping. It does NOT observe live lift lines. Never add copy or logic that
   claims real-time crowd reactivity. The model forecasts crowd pressure.

3. SCORES DRIVE LABELS, NEVER THE REVERSE. sd-app.js and recommendation-roles.js must derive
   every role and verdict label from actual computed scores. A past bug had labels
   disconnected from scores (e.g. a "Worth a Look" surfacing an obvious destination, or a
   verdict that contradicted the number). Any edit to roles or labels must reference real
   computed values, never hardcoded logic.

Rules:
- Never add a scoring dimension without wiring it into BOTH sd-scoring.js AND the consumers
  (recommendation-roles.js and sd-app.js).
- Never change how normalizedWeights() aggregates input without explicit instruction.
- Always check: does the assigned role match what the score actually says?

### AI MUST NEVER TOUCH THE SCORING PATH
AI/LLM generation is used for COPY ONLY (newsletter text, resort page prose). It must never
read from, write to, compute, or influence: sd-scoring.js, recommendation-roles.js,
/api/weights.js, the crowd model, or role assignment in sd-app.js. Determinism and
transparency are the product's trust foundation. If a request would route any generated or
model-derived value into a score, role, or ranking position, STOP and flag it before writing
any code.

