## DATA INTEGRITY RULES

- Resort coordinates must be accurate. Past bugs placed resorts in the wrong state.
- Pricing data should reflect actual lift ticket prices, not placeholder values.
- Summit elevation, vertical drop, trail counts, snowfall averages, and lift capacity are
  factual fields. Do not generate or estimate these. Flag missing data instead.
- When editing resorts.js, preserve the existing object structure exactly. Adding a field to
  one resort means adding it (even if null) to every resort, for consistency.

### Known data issue (not yet fixed)
- A geographic sanity cap is NOT yet implemented. Late-season scores plus near-zero crowd can
  push geographically nonsensical picks into a region (e.g. Eaglecrest, Alaska surfacing in
  the West newsletter pick with absurd drive times). Until the cap exists, sanity-check any
  region-level pick for geographic plausibility before shipping.

