## SEO ARCHITECTURE - DO NOT BREAK

The site has a deliberate SEO content structure built for organic discovery.

Pages that exist and must stay intact:
- One individual resort page per mountain (currently 300)
- One state landing page per state (currently 37)
- City / drive-origin landing pages (e.g. /from/boston.html, /from/new-york.html)
- Ski pass comparison hub and regional comparison pages
- robots.txt at root
- sitemap.xml (must stay current - regenerate if new pages are added)

Canonical tag rules:
- Every page must have <link rel="canonical"> pointing to its own non-www URL
- The canonical domain is wheretoskinext.com (no www)
- Never create a page without a canonical tag

Navigation must be consistent across all page types. If you change the nav on one template,
flag that it needs to propagate to all templates.

### On the horizon: GEO (generative engine optimization)
Batch AI content generation grounded in per-mountain differentiating data, to make the
300-mountain dataset citable by AI search engines. This is COPY generation only and is still
governed by the "AI must never touch the scoring path" rule above. Note: generate-resort-
content.js is the current AI-detection risk, because its helpers return only a few fixed
strings per bracket and produce near-identical paragraphs across mountains. Per-mountain
grounded generation is the intended fix.

