## DOMAIN AUTHORITY

When a scoring result conflicts with the operator's on-the-ground knowledge (e.g. a small
mountain outranking a major resort), FLAG it and ask before changing anything. Do not
auto-calibrate the model around a single surprising result. Non-compensatory outputs that
look surprising are often correct (see the scoring section). The operator decides whether a
surprising result is a real bug or the model working as designed.

