- normalizedWeights() returning hardcoded fixed weights instead of input-derived weights,
  making the engine non-functional.
- JSON.parse() failing silently on JS object literal syntax in data files. Fixed by switching
  to vm.runInNewContext(). Do not revert this.
- Role / verdict labels disconnected from actual computed scores, producing contradictory
  output. Fixed by unifying score references.
- The "Worth a Look" role surfacing obvious destinations (Killington, Stowe, Loon, etc).
  Fixed with the three-signal obviousness test (destinationClass, passGroup, metroGravity).
- Resort coordinates placed in the wrong state. Always verify lat/lng when adding or editing.
- www vs non-www canonical mismatch causing duplicate indexing. All canonicals are non-www.
  Vercel redirects www to non-www.

